<title>USA: Bre-X named in another class-action suit.</title>
<headline>Bre-X named in another class-action suit.</headline>
<dateline>NEW YORK 1997-04-01</dateline>
<text>
<p>Bre-X Minerals Ltd was named on Tuesday in another purported class-action lawsuit alleging the Canadian company and some of its officers overstated gold reserves in the Busang project in Indonesia.</p>
<p>A number of lawsuits have been filed against Bre-X in recent days, following reports that the Busang find may not be as big as originally thought.</p>
<p>The latest lawsuit was filed by Wechsler Harwood Halebian &amp; Feffer LLP, on behalf of people who bought Bre-X shares from August 19, 1996 through March 26, 1997.</p>
